The paper proposes a method for estimating prediction uncertainty in a pre-trained neural network model, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of uncertainty estimation. The method involves estimating the training data density in representation space, which is a technique used in density estimation and clustering. The model is then trained to predict in-distribution errors and detect out-of-distribution data, which falls under the categories of classification and anomaly detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also possible due to the use of neural networks and natural language processing in the paper.
